&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Payment Operations team is part of the broader Payments &amp;amp; Strategic Partnerships Team and ensures payments are processed securely, accurately, and timely, while balancing customer experience, growth, and compliance. As a Payment Operations Analyst, Assoc, you will play a key role in supporting both payment operations and legal operations workflows that protect BILL, our customers, and our partners. This role is responsible for executing high-accuracy operational processes, including payment exception handling and legal request processing such as liens, garnishments, bankruptcies, subpoenas, data pulls, and other legal inquiries. You will work both independently and cross-functionally with Legal, Compliance, Risk, Support, and Operations teams to ensure requests are handled within service levels, in accordance with policy, and with strong attention to detail.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d love to chat if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process and manage legal operations workflows including liens, garnishments, bankruptcies, subpoenas, levies, data pulls, and other legal inquiries in accordance with internal procedures and regulatory requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, validate, and complete payment and legal requests with a high degree of accuracy, ensuring appropriate documentation, tracking, and timely resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Legal, Compliance, Risk, Support, and other cross-functional teams to research requests, resolve exceptions, and support escalations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailed case records, audit trails, and supporting documentation for legal and operational activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate payment exceptions and account-related issues, identify root causes, and take action to resolve or escalate them appropriately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor queues and service levels to ensure time-sensitive legal requests and payment operations tasks are completed within required deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform data pulls and account research to support internal reviews, external requests, audits, and reporting needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to exercise sound judgment when handling sensitive customer and legal matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify process gaps and recommend improvements that increase control, efficiency, accuracy, and scalability across payment and legal operations workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability

